# Frontend Environment Variables

# Google OAuth Configuration
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Enable the Google+ API
# 4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Web application)
# 5. Add authorized origins:
#    - http://localhost:3000 (development)
#    - Your production domain (e.g., https://yourdomain.com)
# 6. Copy the Client ID below
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=650004366786-3a0jk5vreprju8kkud5qdrdriqm0gkfg.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Backend API Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local in the frontend directory
# 2. Fill in the NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID with your actual Google Client ID
# 3. For production, update NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL to your production backend URL
# 4. Do NOT commit .env.local to version control
